This topic describes how to install and configure Anypoint Platform Service Brokers for PCF.

##<a id='install'></a> Install and Configure Anypoint Platform Service Brokers for PCF

1. Download the product file from Pivotal Network or [MuleSoft's customer portal](https://www.mulesoft.com/support-login).

1. Navigate to the Ops Manager Installation Dashboard and click **Import a Product** to upload the product file.

1. Click **Add** next to the uploaded *Anypoint Platform Service Brokers for PCF* tile in the Ops Manager **Available Products** view to add it to your staging area.

1. Click the newly added **Anypoint Platform Service Brokers for PCF** tile to configure it. See the **Configuring the Tile** section below for details.

1. Click **Save**.

1. Return to the Ops Manager Installation Dashboard and click **Apply Changes** to install *Anypoint Platform Service Brokers for PCF* tile.



##<a id='configure'></a> Configuring the Tile

In order to set up your tile, you will need to first obtain the following:

1. Download the default Stem Cell from Pivotal and upload it as a .zip file
1. Generate a runtime license digest using MuleSoft License Verifier service. See the section [Licence](index.html#licence) for instructions on how to do this
1. Credentials for your [Anypoint Platform organization](https://docs.mulesoft.com/access-management/organization). To obtain these:
..1. Login to the Anypoint Platform as a user with admin rights
..1. Go to **Access Management** > **Organization**
..1. Open the settings for your main organization and copy the following values: `clientId`, `clientSecret`, `orgId`


Below are the configurable settings on your Tile. These fields come with default values that you will likely need to change for your particular use case.

[table]:

| Property | Description |
| --------- | ------------ |
| MULE_LICENSE|Paste the contents of the `muleLicenseKey.lic` file you generated on the MuleSoft License Verifier service. See section [Licence](index.html#licence). |
| SUPER_USER_CREDS_CLIENTID | `clientId` on Anypoint platform. Obtain it by doing as described above |
| SUPER_USER_CREDS_CLIENTSECRET | `clientSecret` to access Anypoint platform. Obtain it by doing as described above |
| SUPER_USER_CREDS_MASTERORGID | `orgId` for your organization on the Anypoint platform. Obtain it by doing as described above. If you have more than one because you will manage multiple top-level organizations and want to run each on a different PCF space, you must install multiple separate tiles and configure one with each.|
| ANYPOINT_PLATFORM_PLATFORM_BASE_URI | URI under which you host the Anypoint Platform on your local network |
| ANYPOINT_PLATFORM_CORESERVICES_BASE_URI | URI under which you host the Core Services for the Anypoint Platform on your local network |
| ANYPOINT_PLATFORM_ARMBASEURI | URI under which you host the Runtime Manager on your local network |


The following properties are required by Runtime Manager service broker. These properties need to be unique per PCF installation:

| Property | Description |
| --------- | ------------ |
| CF_SERVICE_NAME | Runtime manager service broker service name |
| CF_SERVICE_ID | Runtime manager service broker service id |
| CF_SERVICE_PLAN | Runtime manager service broker service plan |

The following properties are required by the API Gateway service broker. These properties need to be unique per PCF installation:

| Property | Description |
| --------- | ------------ |
| GATEWAY_SERVICE_NAME | API gateway service broker service name |
| GATEWAY_SERVICE_ID | API gateway service broker service id |
| GATEWAY_SERVICE_PLAN | API gateway service broker service plan |



